Book.Body:
We want to show an image of a triangle:


    \begin{tikzpicture}
        \coordinate (A) at (0,0);
        \coordinate (B) at (1,0);
        \coordinate (C) at (0,2);
        \draw (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- cycle;
    \end{tikzpicture}


After the image we put another one.


    \begin{tikzpicture}
        \draw[blue, thick] (0,0) -> (2,3);
    \end{tikzpicture}


This ends our minimal example.
